## Troubleshooting — Errors We Hit and How We Fixed Them
| Error | Cause | Fix |
|---|---|---|
| `Unable to find type [GodPotato.Program]` | Wrong class name for the assembly | Use `$asm.EntryPoint.Invoke()` instead — no class name needed |
| `Object of type 'System.Object[]' cannot be converted to type 'System.String[]'` | Args not cast as string array | Add `[string[]]` cast: `@(,[string[]]@('-cmd','whoami'))` |
| `Win32Error:225` | Defender caught the exe (virus detected) | Disable Defender first as SYSTEM, then re-run |
| `Assembly.Load` succeeds but no output | Webshell doesn't show stdout | Pipe output to file: `| Out-File C:\Windows\Tasks\out.txt` |
| GodPotato shows `CurrentUser: NT AUTHORITY\SYSTEM` but command fails | The `-cmd` command itself has issues | Prefix with `cmd /c` for cmd commands, or use full paths |
| `DownloadData` fails | HTTP server not running or firewall | Check `python3 -m http.server 80` is running, check outbound connectivity |
| `mcs` compilation fails on Kali | Mono not installed | `sudo apt install mono-devel -y` |
| `mcs` fails with System.Net reference error | Missing `-r:System.dll` for IPv4 loader | Add `-r:System.dll` flag to mcs command |
| Meterpreter doesn't connect back | Handler not running or wrong port/IP | Verify handler is listening, check LHOST/LPORT match |
